assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Nac Co., Ltd. engages in the water delivery and housing businesses in Japan. The company produces and sells home delivery water and hypochlorous acid aqueous solution; and provides finance and insurance services. It also rents and sells dust control products, such as mops and mats, nursing care and welfare equipment, and pest control equipment; and undertakes regular cleaning work and construction contracts for custom-built detached houses. In addition, the company constructs and sells construction-related know-how products and building materials to local builders, consulting business, and housing franchise business; installs and sells energy-saving related materials; offers building maintenance services; develops, manufactures, and sells cosmetics and nutritional supplements; and sells condominiums. Further, it engages in the mail-order sale of cosmetics, health foods, beauty materials, etc. The company was formerly known as Duskin Tsurugawa Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Nac Co., Ltd. in 1977. The company was incorporated in 1971 and is based in Tokyo, Japan.
